A fire has razed down part of a popular tourist restaurant Bidibadu in Diani on Monday. Police said the 1.30pm fire might have been caused by an electrical fault. "It started at the kitchen roof and quickly spread to the dining area, food store and four rooms," Msambweni OCPD Joseph Chebust said. Revellers were safely evacuated to safety after the fire broke out. The restaurant roof is thatched with Coastal popular Makuti, which is highly flammable. Kwale fire brigade and revellers at the restaurant helped put the fire off. The restaurant situated along the Indian Ocean near the vast world renown Diani Beach is popular for tourist water sporting activities like windsurfing, snorkelling and diving. No one was injured during the incidence. Click here for the latest political news